<subSubSection pageNumber="398" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="398">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="398">Note:</emphasis>
Turland (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="398">Taxon</emphasis>
44: 419. 1995) proposed the name for rejection but Greuter &amp; Scholz (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="398">Taxon</emphasis>
45: 522. 1996) described the Cretan plant figured by Alpino as a new species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Scholz" authorityName="Scholz" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Phragmites" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="398">Phragmites frutescens</emphasis>
Scholz
</taxonomicName>
, thereby blocking the possibility of a transfer of the Linnaean epithet, and making the proposal unnecessary. The Committee for Spermatophyta (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="398">Taxon</emphasis>
47: 863. 1998) therefore did not recommend acceptance of the proposal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
